OL,6,F"Police intervene before he tries to
OL,7,Fdo it again. He then abuses several
OL,8,Fofficers and says he will flick a
OL,9,Fcigarette at them.
OL,11,F"He then tells them he hopes they get
OL,12,Fhit by a brick and that he feels like
OL,13,Flifting up one of their helmets and
OL,14,Fsmacking them over the chin."
OL,16,FRoughley, who had a number of previous
OL,17,Fyouth convictions including assaulting
OL,18,Fan emergency worker and racially
OL,19,Faggravated threatening behaviour, was
OL,20,Falso on police bail at the time of the
OL,21,Foffence, the court heard.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/8
